## Memory System

You have a persistent memory database at http://${DOCKER_HOST_IP}:${MEMORY_API_PORT}.

```bash
# Search memories
curl -s "http://${DOCKER_HOST_IP}:${MEMORY_API_PORT}/memory/search?q=<query>&agent=${AGENT_ID}"

# Save a memory
curl -s -X POST http://${DOCKER_HOST_IP}:${MEMORY_API_PORT}/memory/write \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"table": "memories", "action": "insert", "agent": "${AGENT_ID}", "data": {"category": "System", "type": "semantic", "content": "thing to remember", "confidence": 0.9}}'

# Save session state
curl -s -X POST http://${DOCKER_HOST_IP}:${MEMORY_API_PORT}/memory/session-state \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"agent": "${AGENT_ID}", "task_summary": "what we did", "status": "completed", "context": "key details"}'
```

## MCP Gateway (MetaMCP)

MCP tools are available via the `mcporter` CLI. The gateway aggregates all MCP servers behind one endpoint.

```bash
# List all available MCP tools
mcporter list

# Call a tool
mcporter call <server>.<tool> --arg value

# Example: search Gmail
mcporter call google-workspace.gmail_search --query "invoices"
```

mcporter is pre-configured to connect to the gateway at http://${DOCKER_HOST_IP}:${MCP_GATEWAY_PORT}.

